Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.33,0:00:24.62,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.23,0:00:28.75,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You're late.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.75,0:00:31.68,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,You defeated Aura, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.56,0:00:50.06,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Like a fairy tale
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.06,0:00:52.48,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,It's a sign the story has reached its end
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.48,0:00:55.40,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Like a single passage taken from
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.40,0:00:57.03,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,A journey that was too long
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.03,0:00:59.36,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Of the evil that once cast a shadow
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.36,0:01:01.70,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Across this land
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.70,0:01:04.03,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,And the memories of the short journey
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.03,0:01:06.50,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,With the hero who defeated it
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.29,0:01:16.26,Signs,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1,473)\blur0.25\fs25\fnGeorgia\fsp3.9\pos(322,230)\c&HFFFCFE&\t(989,4326,\c&HEFC777&)\t(6411,6745,\c&HEAC732&)}Beyond Journey's End
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.51,0:01:18.80,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,The story ends
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.80,0:01:21.30,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,And the hero goes to sleep
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.30,0:01:24.14,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Leaving this land with
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.14,0:01:25.81,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Days of peace and quiet
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.81,0:01:28.31,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,The passage of time heartlessly
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.31,0:01:30.48,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Makes people forget
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.48,0:01:33.27,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Even the tracks left behind by his life
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.27,0:01:35.07,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Begin to rust
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.07,0:01:36.90,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Just the same
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.90,0:01:39.20,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Your words and wishes and courage
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.20,0:01:42.53,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Are still inside of me
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.53,0:01:44.41,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,And they live on
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.20,0:01:46.95,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,We chose the same path
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.95,0:01:49.08,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,That's all it was supposed to be
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.08,0:01:50.62,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Why is it that at some point
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.62,0:01:54.88,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to understand the reason for
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.88,0:01:56.25,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,The tears that fall down my cheeks
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.25,0:01:57.34,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Even now
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.34,0:01:59.72,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,If I retrace the journey we walked together
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.72,0:02:03.26,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Even though you're not there
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.26,0:02:04.93,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I know I'll be able to find it
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.41,0:02:26.11,Default,GRANAT,0000,0000,0000,,I don't believe—\NI {\i1}can't{\i0} believe this happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.11,0:02:27.07,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.68,0:02:30.19,Default,GRANAT,0000,0000,0000,,Wait. You don't need to run.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.82,0:02:33.58,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,The graf said he'd pardon you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.31,0:02:38.34,Default,GRANAT,0000,0000,0000,,It must have been a fierce battle,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.52,0:02:41.85,Default,GRANAT,0000,0000,0000,,but none of them are seriously damaged.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.91,0:02:51.09,Default,GRANAT,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for treating the heroes \Nof the northern lands with respect.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.04,0:02:59.32,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I used to cast flashier spells, \Nbut Himmel got mad at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.60,0:03:01.35,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I bet he did.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.35,0:03:04.32,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,He was right to be angry. I'd be angry, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.75,0:03:08.11,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Himmel trained you well.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.11,0:03:09.71,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Don't say it like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.59,0:03:13.28,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I guess you're right, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.31,0:03:18.70,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,This is a normal reaction.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.21,0:03:20.78,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.77,0:03:23.42,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.67,0:03:27.05,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Fern, Stark.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.51,0:03:29.79,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Good job defeating Lügner and his henchwoman.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.32,0:03:31.56,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm proud of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.07,0:03:38.90,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I'd be even more impressed \Nif you weren't so beat up, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.90,0:03:41.06,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,This is normal for a warrior.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.06,0:03:43.05,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,What does "normal" even mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.05,0:03:44.70,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You're covered in wounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.16,0:03:49.50,Default,GRANAT,0000,0000,0000,,See that they receive proper burials. \NI'll escort our benefactors to the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.50,0:03:50.34,Default,GUARD A,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, milord.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.70,0:03:51.62,Default,GUARD B,0000,0000,0000,,Milord.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.84,0:03:53.96,Default,GRANAT,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.61,0:04:06.93,Default,GRANAT,0000,0000,0000,,Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.34,0:04:11.72,Default,GRANAT,0000,0000,0000,,I've never been as grateful to anyone \Nas I am to you today.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.25,0:04:32.10,Default,GRANAT,0000,0000,0000,,Frieren, I promised to reward you \Nin any way I could.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.39,0:04:38.08,Default,GRANAT,0000,0000,0000,,You requested the defensive \Nbarrier grimoire by Flamme
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.08,0:04:43.12,Default,GRANAT,0000,0000,0000,,that has been passed down \Nfor generations in my family.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.59,0:04:47.63,Default,GRANAT,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure this is what you want? \NThis grimoire...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.63,0:04:48.96,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's fake.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.17,0:04:54.45,Default,GRANAT,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. The defensive barrier it describes
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.45,0:04:58.66,Default,GRANAT,0000,0000,0000,,is nothing like our city's barrier, \Nwhose spell is passed down by oral tradition.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.38,0:05:01.57,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm well aware of that, milord.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.57,0:05:03.28,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's just my hobby.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.02,0:05:05.15,Default,GRANAT,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.29,0:05:09.98,Default,GRANAT,0000,0000,0000,,Either way, you needn't use \Nsuch formal language.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.98,0:05:13.53,Default,GRANAT,0000,0000,0000,,From your perspective, \NI must seem akin to an infant.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.25,0:05:18.42,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I suffered a bitter experience when \NI first left to defeat the Demon King.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.73,0:05:22.08,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, Mr. Heiter \Nsaid that in the royal capital,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.08,0:05:25.49,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,disrespecting nobility \Nis punishable by death.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.94,0:05:31.05,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Himmel and Eisen were nearly executed \Nfor speaking casually to the king.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.88,0:05:35.65,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Remembering Himmel screaming \Nand crying takes me back.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.98,0:05:39.55,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Execution? That's extreme.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.16,0:05:45.64,Flashback,GRANAT,0000,0000,0000,,And speaking so casually to me \Nis a serious crime in this town, brat.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.87,0:05:47.27,Flashback,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, old man.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.27,0:05:49.47,Flashback,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna break this \Nexpensive-looking chair.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.17,0:05:54.58,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Th-The central lands sure \Nare barbaric, milord.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.39,0:05:59.95,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.24,0:06:02.73,Default,GARDENER,0000,0000,0000,,I've finished cutting the \Ntrees in the backyard.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.73,0:06:03.71,Default,GRANAT,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.01,0:06:09.96,Default,GRANAT,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you know, I only said that \Nso you'd escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.46,0:06:14.85,Default,GRANAT,0000,0000,0000,,In this town, you won't be thrown \Nin prison just for speaking casually.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.21,0:06:17.16,Default,GRANAT,0000,0000,0000,,Be at ease.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.73,0:06:19.79,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,In that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.79,0:06:22.10,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Good news for you, Mr. Stark.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.24,0:06:26.85,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,He's passed out.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.32,0:06:36.49,Default,GRANAT,0000,0000,0000,,I've told the townsfolk of Aura's defeat.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.49,0:06:39.97,Default,GRANAT,0000,0000,0000,,They all want to honor the heroes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.46,0:06:42.55,Default,GRANAT,0000,0000,0000,,I ask that you take your time here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.27,0:06:54.87,Default,CHILD,0000,0000,0000,,He's floating.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.76,0:07:00.27,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,It's not that big a deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.15,0:07:13.31,Songs_Insert,INSERT LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,The name that has protected me
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.31,0:07:20.56,Songs_Insert,INSERT LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Is being called by that soothing voice of yours
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.56,0:07:27.75,Songs_Insert,INSERT LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,So that you won't close your eyes all alone
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.75,0:07:35.00,Songs_Insert,INSERT LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I'll embrace you
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.00,0:07:41.99,Songs_Insert,INSERT LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,You joined your warm hands with mine
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.99,0:07:48.05,Songs_Insert,INSERT LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,So I won't forget
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.05,0:07:55.19,Songs_Insert,INSERT LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Beyond the night, where it's full of flowers
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.19,0:08:02.41,Songs_Insert,INSERT LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,It is where you are, a place I will return to
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.41,0:08:10.02,Songs_Insert,INSERT LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Split the swelling, unravel the darkness
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.02,0:08:18.00,Songs_Insert,INSERT LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,So that the dream remains uncorrupted
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.00,0:08:23.44,Songs_Insert,INSERT LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,To the blue path that never ends
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.44,0:08:25.06,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I finished the shopping.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.05,0:08:28.13,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Shall we go, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.96,0:08:31.91,Default,GRANAT,0000,0000,0000,,You're leaving already, Frieren?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.91,0:08:33.39,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Graf Granat.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.48,0:08:37.97,Default,GRANAT,0000,0000,0000,,I'll see you to the gates.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.15,0:08:44.86,Default,GRANAT,0000,0000,0000,,Frieren, I hear you're traveling to Ende,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.86,0:08:48.07,Default,GRANAT,0000,0000,0000,,the farthest point north, \Nwhere the Demon King's castle is.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.34,0:08:54.34,Default,GRANAT,0000,0000,0000,,But currently, conditions on the \NNorthern Plateau aren't looking good.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.65,0:08:57.18,Default,GRANAT,0000,0000,0000,,Travel is restricted.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.59,0:09:02.86,Default,GRANAT,0000,0000,0000,,Even adventurers must be accompanied \Nby a first-class mage.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.12,0:09:06.80,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Then there should no problem \Nwith Ms. Frieren by our side.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.80,0:09:09.72,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,What's a first-class mage?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.72,0:09:12.25,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Frieren, you don't know?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.85,0:09:17.18,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,It's a certification awarded by the \NContinental Magic Association.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.18,0:09:18.26,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Certification?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.26,0:09:21.53,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I acquired mine in the \Nholy capital when we left.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.46,0:09:23.35,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.74,0:09:26.21,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,This is my third-class mage certificate.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.68,0:09:30.09,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, you did have \Nsome business to take care of then.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.09,0:09:32.54,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Is this what certifications \Nlook like these days?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.54,0:09:37.10,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Frieren, don't tell me you're \Nan uncertified underground mage.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.10,0:09:39.40,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Don't make it sound like \NI'm some back-alley doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.95,0:09:44.41,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,The organizations that regulate \Nmages are constantly changing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.41,0:09:47.04,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I can't be bothered obtaining \Na new certification every time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.86,0:09:51.28,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt this holy emblem works anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.66,0:09:55.46,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,What is that antique?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.46,0:09:59.00,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Even I know about the \NContinental Magic Association.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.00,0:10:01.92,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,They've been around for over \Nhalf a century at the very least.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.92,0:10:03.78,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,That's barely anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.28,0:10:08.72,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's a hassle when they change their \Nstandards of conduct so frequently.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.12,0:10:12.01,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, we'll need to overcome \Nthis problem before we continue.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.47,0:10:15.80,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know the specifics,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.80,0:10:17.93,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,but I believe there's a place \Nin the northern lands
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.93,0:10:20.65,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,where you can take the first-class exam.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.41,0:10:26.49,Default,GRANAT,0000,0000,0000,,The largest magical city in the \Nnorthern lands, Äußerst.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.74,0:10:30.42,Default,GRANAT,0000,0000,0000,,It's far beyond the Schwer Mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.90,0:10:35.22,Default,GRANAT,0000,0000,0000,,You can follow the highway, \Nbut it'll be a long journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.85,0:10:43.44,Default,GRANAT,0000,0000,0000,,Frieren, the house of Granat will \Nnever forget what you've done for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.18,0:10:47.49,Default,GRANAT,0000,0000,0000,,Safe travels.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.99,0:11:02.32,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,It's snowing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.73,0:11:04.43,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,It's almost winter.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.00,0:11:09.11,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,The winters around here are bitter, \Nso be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.46,0:11:11.33,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,If you underestimate them, you'll die.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.33,0:11:13.09,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Is it really that dangerous?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.20,0:11:15.60,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.09,0:11:20.11,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,In the war against the Demon King's forces, \Nwhat do you think claimed the most lives?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.65,0:11:22.98,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It was the winters of the northern lands.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.36,0:11:32.61,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,See? We're lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.45,0:11:38.76,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,What are we going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.97,0:11:42.97,Signs_EpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur0.2\c&HFAFFF7&\pos(359,270.5)}Episode 11: Winter in the Northern Lands
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.89,0:11:47.22,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,We're lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.47,0:11:52.98,Signs_WText,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur0.2\pos(588.5,16)}28 years after the death of Himmel the Hero,\Nin the Decke region, located in the northern lands
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.95,0:11:52.99,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe we got lost before \Neven entering the Schwer Mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.00,0:11:56.55,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Stark, wake up!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.55,0:11:57.73,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,If you fall asleep, you'll die!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.51,0:12:04.01,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Have jumbo-berry specials \Nalways been this small?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.01,0:12:05.36,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Who cares about that right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.51,0:12:07.82,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,What should we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.45,0:12:12.75,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,In these strong winds, \Nwe can't transport him with magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.14,0:12:15.39,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,He'd probably be blown away.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.79,0:12:19.14,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Then we'll have to carry him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.72,0:12:26.99,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,He's heavy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.69,0:12:30.38,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Why is he so heavy?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.32,0:12:33.15,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,You smell nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.15,0:12:34.90,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Can I leave him behind?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.90,0:12:36.01,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Bear it for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.43,0:12:39.63,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,There should be an emergency shelter \Nat the foot of the mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.63,0:12:42.64,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that information \Neighty years out of date?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.23,0:12:44.86,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Are we going to be all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.02,0:12:53.28,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.90,0:12:57.06,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's still being maintained regularly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.89,0:13:04.35,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,It seems like someone's inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.35,0:13:06.49,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps someone arrived before us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.49,0:13:08.54,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,We're going inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.54,0:13:10.63,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,We'll freeze out here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.60,0:13:17.63,Default,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,Good! Very good!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.63,0:13:19.02,Default,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,I'm starting to feel warmer!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.31,0:13:27.65,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse the intrusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.94,0:13:34.79,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Frieren, we can't stay here. \NLet's look for someplace else.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.79,0:13:36.57,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,What? Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.57,0:13:38.65,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,There's a pervert inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.34,0:13:41.65,Default,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,A pervert? That's awfully rude.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.30,0:13:45.55,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go, Ms. Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.63,0:13:49.24,Default,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,Wait. Are you an elf?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.00,0:13:58.32,Default,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,It's been about 300 years since \NI've met another of my kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.71,0:14:01.96,Default,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,I thought the elves had already died out.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.96,0:14:03.48,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,So did I.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.16,0:14:06.68,Default,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,And thanks for the fire, miss.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.30,0:14:08.31,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.74,0:14:11.62,Default,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,I'm lucky I ran into a couple of mages.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.92,0:14:14.92,Default,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,The Goddess must have led you here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.65,0:14:21.11,Default,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,I crossed the Schwer Mountains, \Nbut this blizzard extinguished my coals.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.11,0:14:25.22,Default,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,I was keeping myself alive by doing \Nsquats inside this freezing hut.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.58,0:14:26.76,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.21,0:14:29.21,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sure I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.99,0:14:31.97,Default,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Kraft the Monk.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.23,0:14:34.29,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Frieren the Mage.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.29,0:14:36.59,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Fern, also a mage.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.54,0:14:39.73,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,This is Mr. Stark the Warrior.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.74,0:14:42.68,Default,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, Aureole, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.68,0:14:44.51,Default,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,You're traveling to heaven, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.39,0:14:47.94,Default,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,Good on you for being so pious.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.48,0:14:50.41,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sure I totally believe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.93,0:14:52.15,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.93,0:14:54.82,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Stark is getting colder.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.32,0:15:03.66,DefaultItalics,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,So warm and comfortable...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.95,0:15:09.22,DefaultItalics,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,And that's one huge jumbo-berry special.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.12,0:15:14.02,DefaultItalics,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,What happened to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.31,0:15:17.60,DefaultItalics,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,We got caught in a blizzard, and then...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.50,0:15:36.62,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Who is this guy?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.75,0:15:40.86,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You're so noisy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.22,0:15:46.60,Default,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,That's no way to thank someone \Nfor warming you up with their body.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.60,0:15:48.61,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Their body?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.88,0:15:53.49,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,You've got a nice body, old man.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.49,0:15:54.62,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Stark?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.62,0:15:56.64,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,No, not like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.63,0:16:00.36,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I mean he's got a nice body \Nfrom training hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.04,0:16:03.98,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,You must be really strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.43,0:16:06.02,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,What's your name?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.88,0:16:08.57,Default,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,Kraft the Monk.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.27,0:16:11.35,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I've never heard of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.06,0:16:15.16,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,But you must be a pretty famous monk, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.25,0:16:19.98,Default,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,Stark, rest here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.59,0:16:23.27,Default,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,You two, help me bring in food supplies.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.83,0:16:26.66,Default,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,My wagon and cargo are nearby.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.54,0:16:32.00,Default,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,I'm really glad I met all of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.35,0:16:35.34,Default,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,We'll be able to use these frozen supplies.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.77,0:16:37.40,Default,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,Use as much as you'd like.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.02,0:16:40.09,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,You've certainly stocked up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.51,0:16:44.14,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Trying to cross the Schwer Mountains \Nin these conditions would be suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.82,0:16:47.22,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,We're stuck here for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.96,0:16:53.62,Default,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, Frieren, do you know who I am?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.62,0:16:54.91,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.91,0:16:55.94,Default,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.36,0:16:59.17,Default,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know the first thing \Nabout you, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.56,0:17:02.27,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,She's the mage from the party of heroes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.76,0:17:04.11,Default,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,And before that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.28,0:17:07.01,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.72,0:17:10.04,Default,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,I mean that we're elves.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.59,0:18:01.54,Default,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,It's been nearly six months.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.35,0:18:07.57,Default,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to all of you, we made it through \Nthe long winter in the northern lands.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.17,0:18:10.22,Default,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,Take this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.06,0:18:18.33,Default,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,Give it to Fern. She's a pious girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.93,0:18:21.39,Default,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,Must be because she was raised by a priest.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.09,0:18:24.62,Default,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,She never forgets to thank the Goddess.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.48,0:18:28.41,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Kraft, why do you believe in the Goddess?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.61,0:18:32.79,Default,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,You don't, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.41,0:18:37.50,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Excluding during the age of mythology,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.50,0:18:43.11,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,the Goddess of Creation hasn't shown herself \Nonce in the long history of this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.06,0:18:47.88,Default,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,You're young. I used to think that way, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.46,0:18:52.55,Default,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,But now I believe in the Goddess \Nfrom the bottom of my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.80,0:18:57.06,Default,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,No, I need her to exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.10,0:19:04.24,Default,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone who knew of my \Nrighteous triumphs has died.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.49,0:19:10.20,Default,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,So when I die, I'll go to heaven \Nand the Goddess will praise me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.31,0:19:13.83,Default,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,She'll say, "Well done, Kraft."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.43,0:19:18.91,Default,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,"You lived a fantastic life."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.26,0:19:23.47,Default,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,You understand that, Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.32,0:19:30.80,Default,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,It's too cruel for the path your life took \Nto not be remembered by anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.64,0:19:36.23,Default,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,We've lived a long time to get to this point.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.65,0:19:42.80,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Kraft, that's just something we desire.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.15,0:19:45.12,Default,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.53,0:19:50.11,Default,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,Does that apply to heaven too, Frieren?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.72,0:19:57.89,Default,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,No matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.45,0:20:01.75,Default,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me about yourself, \Nand I'll tell you about myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.16,0:20:08.50,Default,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't believe in the Goddess, \Nthen I'll praise you instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.41,0:20:14.01,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,Are you surprised?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.01,0:20:20.03,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I didn't think you'd fund the \Nreconstruction of this village's orphanage.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.28,0:20:23.85,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,You don't beat around the bush, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.87,0:20:27.01,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,I was an orphan, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.73,0:20:36.54,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure the Goddess will praise me \Nfor living a pure and proper life.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.02,0:20:41.06,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about, you corrupt \Npriest? You're drinking right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.00,0:20:43.07,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.30,0:20:47.54,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have someone to praise you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.30,0:20:50.05,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Where did that come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.48,0:20:54.27,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,You don't seem to believe in the Goddess,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.08,0:20:59.48,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,so if you tell me about yourself, \NI'll praise you instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.37,0:21:02.64,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't done much with my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.10,0:21:05.82,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't done anything praiseworthy.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.22,0:21:08.82,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,Even though you're constantly \Nsuppressing your mana?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.95,0:21:15.51,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,To me, that seems like the \Nresult of tremendous effort.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.45,0:21:19.21,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,Something that would take \Na lifetime to accomplish.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.44,0:21:22.28,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You noticed?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.28,0:21:25.58,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,How many years have we \Ntraveled together again?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.39,0:21:28.85,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's not an interesting story.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.85,0:21:30.56,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,I don't mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.56,0:21:33.50,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, it sounds like something \Nuseful to know for the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.50,0:21:34.23,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.62,0:21:39.61,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps a child of mine will become a mage.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.59,0:21:44.13,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I thought priests couldn't marry.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.24,0:21:54.92,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Why do so many strange \Npeople serve the Goddess?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.95,0:22:00.38,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I'll pass. I've already had \Nsomeone else praise me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.31,0:22:06.50,Default,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,I see. You have good friends, Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.79,0:22:07.95,Default,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,You should cherish them.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.64,0:22:12.03,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, he's already...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.46,0:22:19.52,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,He's in heaven now.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.06,0:22:22.58,Default,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,Then you'll see him again someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.57,0:22:24.82,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.86,0:22:29.04,Default,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.63,0:22:32.98,Default,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,Frieren, I doubt this is \Nthe last time we'll meet.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.42,0:22:35.91,Default,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,I'll see you in a few centuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.38,0:22:42.91,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Take care, old man! I had fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.79,0:22:47.23,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for the pendant!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.97,0:22:52.51,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,And you alright
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.01,0:22:55.02,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Can you hear me
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.81,0:23:01.90,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Trailing along deserted train tracks
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.90,0:23:04.23,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Crying excessively
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.82,0:23:07.40,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Wanting you to smile
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.40,0:23:13.45,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I hold on to memories I'd like to keep fresh
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.45,0:23:17.16,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,There's something I'd like to tell you
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.16,0:23:19.92,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,With words more precious than a goodbye
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.92,0:23:25.59,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Unremarkable yet special
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.59,0:23:29.13,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,See, things that couldn't have been
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.13,0:23:32.18,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Seen if it weren't for these eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.18,0:23:36.93,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Why? They begin to overflow
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.93,0:23:43.02,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,So, if I were to be born again
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.02,0:23:48.86,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I would surely choose this place once more
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.86,0:23:54.87,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,So, if we were to meet again
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.87,0:24:00.62,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I'd never let you go, I'd choose the present
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.62,0:24:03.58,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Even if no promises were made
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.58,0:24:06.50,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Even if I'm lost in days of loneliness
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.50,0:24:12.68,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Those tears will be alright, \Ndawn will surely break
